        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Dynamic Cooling fan motor running at reduced RPM — year 8 evaporator fan on the MB-series Dynamic Cooling system. The Dynamic Cooling architecture relies on fast forced air-circulation for pull-down; reduced fan speed defeats the system's primary function. Compressor measured within spec. Condenser coils clean (under-cabinet installation in a Bel Air pantry, less dust exposure than the Beverly Hills carpet-adjacent install).</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Evaporator fan motor replacement with OEM Marvel part (in stock on truck for MB-series). Verified Dynamic Cooling pull-down speed on test cycle — restocked the unit and confirmed normal chilled-temperature recovery within design window.</p>
